<item>
            <title>[LU-19244] Debian packaging of Pacemaker resource agents is using wrong permission and install directory</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19244</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The pacemaker resource agent files are scripts that need executable permission but lustre/conf/resource/Makefile.am treats them as DATA, should be SCRIPTS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And debian/lustre-resource-agents.install has a typo in the target directory, usr/lib.ocf/&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus the debian packaged resource agents doesn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
